  "A fireworks manufacturer uses the reaction KClO3 -> KCl + O2 to generate oxygen gas. What is the coefficient of KClO3 when the equation is balanced?": "",
  "The balanced equation is 2KClO3 -> 2KCl + 3O2. The coefficient of KClO3 is 2, yielding 6 oxygen atoms on each side.": "",
  "In a lab, sodium metal is dropped into water producing sodium hydroxide and hydrogen gas. A student writes: Na + H2O -> NaOH + H2. What coefficient should be placed in front of Na to balance this equation?": "",
  "The balanced equation is 2Na + 2H2O -> 2NaOH + H2. A coefficient of 2 in front of Na balances the sodium and hydrogen atoms on both sides.": "",
